20/11/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Officials from 14 Black Sea and Balkan countries gathered at the Vouliagmeni resort outside Athens Friday (18 November) to discuss setting up a common alert and surveillance system to stop the spread of bird flu. Albania, Armenia, Bulgaria, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Georgia, Macedonia, Moldova, Romania, Russia, Serbia-Montenegro and Turkey participated in the forum, along with EU members Greece and Cyprus. EU Health Commissioner Markos Kyprianou also attended the closed-door meeting, as did representatives of WHO and the European Centre for Infectious Diseases. (Makfax, Focus - 20/11/05; ANA - 19/11/05; AFP - 18/11/05)
